MOH Announcement: 23RD JAN 2020


The patient is a 66-year-old Chinese man. The Wuhan resident, who arrived in Singapore with his family on Jan 20, flew from Guangzhou via China Southern flight CZ351.
After arriving in Singapore, the man checked in to Shangri-La's Rasa Sentosa Resort and Spa. On Jan 22, he told hotel staff that he was unwell and was taken to Singapore General Hospital, where he was isolated and diagnosed with pneumonia. He was identified to the Ministry of Health as a suspected Wuhan virus case at 10pm. 

On Jan 23 at 6pm, he tested positive for the new coronavirus. 